trans-unit.source: Handle the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser.DocumentCompleted?displayProperty=fullName> event to receive notification when the new document finishes loading.

The WebBrowserDocumentCompletedEventArgs object passed to the event handler lets you retrieve the location of the new document through the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowserDocumentCompletedEventArgs.Url%2A> property.

When the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser.DocumentCompleted?displayProperty=fullName> event occurs, the new document is fully loaded, which means you can access its contents through the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser.Document%2A?displayProperty=fullName>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser.DocumentText%2A?displayProperty=fullName>, or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser.DocumentStream%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowserDocumentCompletedEventArgs"></xref> class.
A <xref:System.Uri> representing the location of the document that was loaded.
Gets the location of the document to which the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser"></xref> control has navigated.
A <xref:System.Uri> representing the location of the document that was loaded.
